bug.short_desc: Translation fails when the same String-literal is used as an argument in both this.tr() and this.trn()

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1286 minimal example countaing two label, one using this.tr(), one this.trn()
Steps to reproduce the bug:
1. Choose a string-literal which should be translated, i.e. "Hello World".
2. Use this string as an argument in this.tr() in one Class A
3. Use it also with this.trn() in another class B
4. Perform generate.py translation
Two problems will occur:
1. The PO-files are missing the plural form given to this.trn(). 2. In the built app, the strings are not translated accordingly.
Possible Workaround: When you make the two strings different from each other (i.e. add a whitespace to one of them), then it works.
A zipped example project is attached

Fixed. Plural will now be taken into account.
